<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-12">
    <div class="page-header">
      <h1>Stage 1: Insecure login form</h1>
    </div>
    <p>
      Welcome to Steal This App! This app will teach you how to exploit common
      web security bugs so you can avoid making these mistakes in your own
      code.
    </p>
    <p>
      For the first stage we present you an insecure login form. Bypass
      security by either:
      <ul>
        <li>Finding out the password or</li>
        <li>Bypassing the login form</li>
      </ul>
    </p>
    <button class="btn btn-default" onclick="$('.hint').show()">Reveal hint</button>
    <p class="hint">
      View source code of the page.
    </p>
    <form id="login" action="/{{stage2}}" style="margin-top: 10px;">
      Password: <input id="password" type="password">
      <input type="submit" value="Login">
    </form>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
$('#login').on('submit', function(e) {
  var password = $('#password').val();
  if (password !== 'gingerbread') {
    alert('Wrong password!');
    e.preventDefault();
  }
});
</script>
